<doc id="286337" wikidata="Q3405681" url="?curid=286337" title="1940 Governor General's Awards">
<text>The 1940 Governor General&#x27;s Awards for Literary Merit were the fifth rendition of the Governor General&#x27;s Awards, Canada&#x27;s annual national awards program which then comprised literary awards alone. The awards recognized Canadian writers for new English-language works published in Canada during 1940 and were presented in 1941. There were no cash prizes.

There was one award in each of three established categories, which recognized English-language works only.

==Winners==
* Fiction: Ringuet, &quot;Thirty Acres&quot;
* Poetry or drama: E. J. Pratt, &quot;Brébeuf and His Brethren&quot;
* Non-fiction: J. F. C. Wright, &quot;Slava Bohu&quot;

